OL,6,FIs building more prisons the solution?
OL,8,FWhile the most simple answer may be to
OL,9,Fbuild more prisons, increasing the
OL,10,Fnumber of sites may not be the best
OL,11,Flong-term solution.
OL,13,FThe number of people given immediate
OL,14,Fcustodial sentences after being
OL,15,Fconvicted fell by 31% from 98,044 to
OL,16,F67,812 between 2012 to 2022, showing
OL,17,Fthat the increased prison population
OL,18,Fis not a result of more criminals
OL,19,Fbeing convicted, figures from the
OL,20,FParliamentary Office of Science and
OL,21,FTechnology (POST) show.
