OL,6,FWhy are prisons across the UK at
OL,7,Fcapacity?
OL,9,FAn increasing issue affecting
OL,10,Fovercapacity is that nearly one-fifth
OL,11,F(17%) of the prison population is on
OL,12,Fremand, according to figures published
OL,13,Fby the Prison Reform Trust.
OL,15,FThis means that either they are still
OL,16,Fawaiting trial and therefore innocent
OL,17,Funtil proven guilty or awaiting
OL,18,Fsentencing after having been found
OL,19,Fguilty.
