OL,3,CUK prisons are nearly at full
OL,4,Ccapacity, but what can be done?
OL,6,FThere are alternatives to keeping
OL,7,Fthese individuals in custody, such as
OL,8,Fallowing them to be remanded in the
OL,9,Fcommunity as they await trial, while
OL,10,Fstill under strict community
OL,11,Fsupervision such as electronic tagging
OL,12,For having to report to a local police
OL,13,Fstation regularly. Community
OL,14,Fsupervision could significantly reduce
OL,15,Fprison populations.
OL,17,FThe number of people who are recalled
OL,18,Fto prisons after being released also
OL,19,Fremains higher than perhaps necessary,
OL,20,FDr Ward told ITV News.
